All insurers authorized to write health insurance in this state and employer-organized associations that self-insure shall transmit at least annually by July 31 to the commissioner the following information, in a format prescribed by the commissioner, on their insurance experience in this state for the preceding calendar year:
Total premium by product type and market segment;
Total enrollment by product type and market segment;
Total cost of medical claims filed by product type and market segment;
Total amount of medical claims paid by the insurer and insured by product type and market segment;
Total policies canceled by type and the aggregate reasons therefor; and
List of total health and medical services paid for, grouped by types of services and costs:
Total cost per health and medical service per insured group:
Cost paid by insurer;
Cost paid by insured; and
Number of insureds who received each service.
